bug.short_desc: Fedora26 hvm guest got stuck at booting when boots from iso image.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1272880 Fedora26 hvm guest booting log
Description of problem: Created a Fedora 26 hvm guest on Fedora26 Alpha release Xen4 host, it can not boot from "Fedora-Server-dvd-x86_64-26-Alpha-1.7.iso" to install the guest. It may stopped at "Booting SMP configuration" or other phases.
Booting logs(attached the full log in the bug): <snip> [ 0.047000] Last level iTLB entries: 4KB 1024, 2MB 1024, 4MB 1024 [ 0.050000] Last level dTLB entries: 4KB 1024, 2MB 1024, 4MB 1024, 1GB 4 [ 0.053000] Freeing SMP alternatives memory: 32K [ 0.055000] ftrace: allocating 31839 entries in 125 pages [ 0.066000] smpboot: Max logical packages: 1 [ 0.068000] x2apic: IRQ remapping doesn't support X2APIC mode [ 0.070000] ..TIMER: vector=0x30 apic1=0 pin1=2 apic2=0 pin2=0 [ 0.084000] clocksource: xen: mask: 0xffffffffffffffff max_cycles: 0x1cd42e4dffb, max_idle_ns: 881590591483 ns [ 0.088000] installing Xen timer for CPU 0 [ 0.090000] smpboot: CPU0: Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-4790 CPU @ 3.60GHz (family: 0x6, model: 0x3c, stepping: 0x3) [ 0.090000] Performance Events: unsupported p6 CPU model 60 no PMU driver, software events only. [ 0.090000] smp: Bringing up secondary CPUs ... [ 0.090000] installing Xen timer for CPU 1 [ 0.090000] x86: Booting SMP configuration: [ 0.090000] .... node #0, CPUs: #1 [ 0.097037] NMI watchdog: disabled (cpu0): hardware events not enabled [ 0.099005] NMI watchdog: Shutting down hard lockup detector on all cpus [ 0.001000] calibrate_delay_direct() dropping max bogoMips estimate 0 = 5696073 [ 0.001000] [Firmware Bug]: TSC ADJUST differs: Reference CPU0: -2160676478295 CPU1: 0 [ 0.154081] installing Xen timer for CPU 2 [ 0.155050] #2 [ 0.001000] [Firmware Bug]: TSC ADJUST differs: Reference CPU0: -2160676478295 CPU2: 0 [ 0.216060] installing Xen timer for CPU 3 [ 0.217042] #3 [ 0.217004] random: fast init done [ 0.001000] [Firmware Bug]: TSC ADJUST differs: Reference CPU0: -2160676478295 CPU3: 0 [ 0.278010] smp: Brought up 1 node, 4 CPUs [ 0.279004] smpboot: Total of 4 processors activated (28789.66 BogoMIPS) [ 0.280233] sched_clock: Marking stable (280000000, 0)->(1227428454179, -1227148454179)
</snip>
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 4.11.0-0.rc3.git0.2.fc26.x86_64
How reproducible: 100% on my Lenovo ThinkCentre M8500t-N000.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora 26 and xen packages. 2. Boot into xen environment and create the hvm guest configuration file which selects booting Fedora26 iso image. 3. Create the guest and check whether the guest can boot up normally.
Actual results:
It stopped at booting phase.
Expected results: The guest should boot up normally and can do installation after it.
Additional info: Some packages information: # rpm -qa|egrep "xen-4|kernel-4|libvirt-3" kernel-4.11.0-0.rc3.git0.2.fc26.x86_64 libvirt-3.1.0-1.fc26.x86_64 xen-4.8.0-8.fc26.x86_64
Host cpu information: # cat /proc/cpuinfo |more processor : 0 vendor_id : GenuineIntel cpu family : 6 model : 60 model name : Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-4790 CPU @ 3.60GHz
More status of verification. -Host: Fedora 26 xen4. hvm guest: Fedora 25. Fedora25 can boot up normally. -This bug does not exist on my Dell PowerEdge R415 system with AMD cpu installed, so I suspect this is a hardware related problem.
Does Fedora iso boot with vcpus=1?
Have you tried xen 4.8.1? There is a same report on Ubuntu, and the issue should be fixed in xen 4.8.1 https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/xen/+bug/1671760

Thanks, I updated the system to the latest Fedora26 version and now the guest can boot up with 8 vcpus without problem.
My configuration file: <snip> <vcpu placement='static' current='8'>8</vcpu> <source file='/media/fedora26/Fedora-Server-dvd-x86_64-26-Alpha-1.7.iso'/> </snip>
My system version: xen-hypervisor-4.8.1-2.fc26.x86_64 xen-4.8.1-2.fc26.x86_64 kernel-4.11.4-300.fc26.x86_64 libvirt-3.2.1-3.fc26.x86_64
